# Spacing Standards - Neuman Brain Design System

**Last Updated:** November 18, 2025
**Version:** 1.0
**Status:** Active

---

## Overview

This document defines the **spacing system** for the Neuman Brain application. All spacing (padding, margins, gaps) must use these standardized tokens to ensure visual consistency across the entire application.

**Philosophy:** "Anywhere we have a margin/gap, it should be the same width/height as all the other margins." - User directive, January 18, 2025

---

## Spacing Scale

### Core Tokens (Tailwind Config)

All spacing tokens are defined in `tailwind.config.js`:

| Token | Value | Tailwind Class | Use Case |
|-------|-------|---------------|----------|
| `widget-padding` | 16px | `p-widget-padding` | Internal padding for all widgets |
| `content-gap` | 16px | `space-y-content-gap` | Vertical spacing between content sections |
| `button-gap` | 8px | `gap-button-gap` | Gap between buttons in button groups |
| `grid-gap` | 24px | `gap-grid-gap` | Gap between widgets in grid layout |
| `section-margin` | 24px | `mb-section-margin` | Standard section bottom margin |
| `section-margin-lg` | 32px | `mb-section-margin-lg` | Large section bottom margin |
| `form-field-gap` | 12px | `space-y-form-field-gap` | Gap between form fields |
| `form-label-gap` | 8px | `mb-form-label-gap` | Gap between label and input |

### Numeric Fallbacks

For maximum compatibility, numeric Tailwind classes can still be used:

| Numeric Class | Value | Equivalent Token | When to Use |
|---------------|-------|------------------|-------------|
| `p-4` | 16px | `p-widget-padding` | Widget padding (preferred: token) |
| `space-y-4` | 16px | `space-y-content-gap` | Content sections (preferred: token) |
| `gap-2` | 8px | `gap-button-gap` | Button groups (preferred: token) |
| `gap-6` | 24px | `gap-grid-gap` | Widget grids (preferred: token) |
| `mb-6` | 24px | `mb-section-margin` | Section margins (preferred: token) |
| `mb-8` | 32px | `mb-section-margin-lg` | Large sections (preferred: token) |
| `space-y-3` | 12px | `space-y-form-field-gap` | Form fields (preferred: token) |
| `mb-2` | 8px | `mb-form-label-gap` | Form labels (preferred: token) |

**Note:** Numeric classes are acceptable during migration period. Future code should use tokens.

