## Usage Guidelines

### 1. Widget Internal Padding

**Standard:** ALL widgets must use `p-4` (16px) internal padding.

**Examples:**
```tsx
// ✅ Correct
<div className="p-4 bg-surface-light dark:bg-surface-dark rounded-card">
  {/* Widget content */}
</div>

// ❌ Incorrect
<div className="p-3 bg-surface-light dark:bg-surface-dark rounded-card">  {/* Too small */}
<div className="p-6 bg-surface-light dark:bg-surface-dark rounded-card">  {/* Too large */}
```

**Rationale:** Consistent internal padding creates visual harmony across all widgets, making the dashboard feel cohesive.

---

### 2. Content Vertical Spacing

**Standard:** Use `space-y-4` (16px) between content sections within a widget.

**Examples:**
```tsx
// ✅ Correct - Widget with multiple sections
<div className="p-4">
  <div className="space-y-4">  {/* 16px between sections */}
    <section>
      <h3>Tasks (3)</h3>
      <ul className="space-y-3">  {/* 12px between list items */}
        <li>Task 1</li>
        <li>Task 2</li>
        <li>Task 3</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <button className="w-full">View All Tasks</button>
  </div>
</div>

// ❌ Incorrect - Inconsistent spacing
<div className="p-4">
  <div className="space-y-2">  {/* Too tight */}
    <section>...</section>
    <button>...</button>
  </div>
</div>
```

**Rationale:** 16px vertical spacing provides clear visual separation between sections without feeling cramped or wasteful.

---

### 3. List Item Spacing

**Standard:** Use `space-y-3` (12px) between list items (tasks, events, notes).

**Examples:**
```tsx
// ✅ Correct - List of tasks
<ul className="space-y-3">
  <li className="flex items-center gap-2">
    <input type="checkbox" />
    <span>Task 1</span>
  </li>
  <li className="flex items-center gap-2">
    <input type="checkbox" />
    <span>Task 2</span>
  </li>
</ul>

// ❌ Incorrect - Too much spacing
<ul className="space-y-6">  {/* Feels disconnected */}
  <li>Task 1</li>
  <li>Task 2</li>
</ul>
```

**Rationale:** 12px spacing for list items is tighter than section spacing (16px) to show they're related items within the same group.

---

### 4. Button Groups

**Standard:** Use `gap-2` (8px) between buttons in a horizontal group.

**Examples:**
```tsx
// ✅ Correct - Button group
<div className="flex gap-2">
  <button>🎨 Background</button>
  <button>📐 Presets</button>
</div>

// ❌ Incorrect - Too much gap
<div className="flex gap-6">  {/* Buttons feel disconnected */}
  <button>🎨 Background</button>
  <button>📐 Presets</button>
</div>
```

**Rationale:** 8px gap is compact enough to show buttons are related actions, but not so tight they feel crowded.

---

### 5. Widget Grid Layout

**Standard:** Use `gap-6` (24px) between widgets in dashboard grid.

**Examples:**
```tsx
// ✅ Correct - Dashboard grid
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
  <Widget title="Tasks" />
  <Widget title="Calendar" />
  <Widget title="Notes" />
</div>

// ❌ Incorrect - Too tight
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-2">  {/* Widgets feel cramped */}
  ...
</div>
```

**Rationale:** 24px gap provides breathing room between widgets without wasting space. Scales well across mobile/tablet/desktop.

---

### 6. Section Margins

**Standard:** Use `mb-6` (24px) for standard section margins, `mb-8` (32px) for large sections.

**Examples:**
```tsx
// ✅ Correct - Page sections
<div className="container mx-auto px-4">
  <section className="mb-8">  {/* Large section - Page header */}
    <h1 className="text-2xl font-bold">Dashboard</h1>
    <p>Your personal management overview</p>
  </section>

  <section className="mb-6">  {/* Standard section */}
    <h2 className="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Recent Activity</h2>
    {/* Content */}
  </section>

  <section className="mb-6">  {/* Standard section */}
    <h2 className="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Upcoming Events</h2>
    {/* Content */}
  </section>
</div>

// ❌ Incorrect - Inconsistent margins
<section className="mb-4">  {/* Too small */}
<section className="mb-10">  {/* Non-standard value */}
```

**Rationale:**
- `mb-6` (24px): Standard spacing between page sections
- `mb-8` (32px): Emphasized spacing for major sections (page header, feature sections)

---

### 7. Form Field Spacing

**Standard:**
- Between form fields: `space-y-3` (12px)
- Between label and input: `mb-2` (8px)

**Examples:**
```tsx
// ✅ Correct - Form layout
<form className="space-y-3">
  <div>
    <label className="block text-sm mb-2">Task Title</label>
    <input type="text" className="w-full px-3 py-2 border rounded" />
  </div>

  <div>
    <label className="block text-sm mb-2">Description</label>
    <textarea className="w-full px-3 py-2 border rounded" rows={3}></textarea>
  </div>

  <div>
    <label className="block text-sm mb-2">Due Date</label>
    <input type="date" className="w-full px-3 py-2 border rounded" />
  </div>
</form>

// ❌ Incorrect - Inconsistent spacing
<form className="space-y-6">  {/* Too much space between fields */}
  <div>
    <label className="block text-sm mb-4">Task Title</label>  {/* Too much space */}
    <input type="text" />
  </div>
</form>
```

**Rationale:**
- 12px between fields keeps form compact but readable
- 8px between label/input shows they're paired

